no longer doing the update, just adding iasl.  See  https://cr.joyent.us/#/c/3240/

Considering this is likely to go upstream at some point, it'd be nice for the readme to be a little less joyent/SmartOS-specific.  (Even if it still references joyent/acpica as the location for the comparison code)
Will update steps 4 and 5 to be more generic.  The earlier mentions should stay the same until changes to acpica are accepted upstream.

Did this function get moved someplace else? I don't see it in any of the other files you listed as the ones you modified. I'm curious why this function was removed, but the subsequent CloseFile function is still here.
That function is no longer needed and it was breaking the build. I forgot to look for more cruft in the same file. I've done that and removed more cruft.
It looks like we have m4 in the platform but don't compile a proto tools version?  Updating that m4 to support -P and longer buffers seems possible at least.
I'm not so sure that trying to modernize the ancient m4 is the best use of time.  GNU m4 is almost certainly a dependency for illumos-extra and any modern open source that uses m4.
The standard yacc not adequate for this?
It looks like there is a FLEX defined in Makefile.master.  Is that one not adequate for the job?

It is defined as /usr/bin/flex, which does not exist.  It turns out that whatever generates illumos.sh is exporting FLEX=/opt/local/bin/flex into the environment, overriding the value in the makefile.

Perhaps this same approach should be taken for bison and gnu M4.
